texts.text: >The Liberators introduce Cait Sith's army to Camael's group.
I've heard your conditions.
I accept, so spare no effort to defeat Rahab.
Tch. This mess is YOUR fault.
Your act of aggression has injured many of our comrades.
A few words of apology is only proper, no?
...Not an olive branch in sight, that's for damn sure.
Well, the demons see the angels as invaders.
It's hard to overlook that little detail.
Stop it, both of you! We came here to join forces.
Let's set aside our animosity for the sake of our kingdom.
Tch, fine.
I shall respect your kingly authority.
...Thanks, I appreciate it.
We humans will act as witnesses.
You both promise to unite against Rahab. Got it?
Understood.
Right. Let's defeat him toge—
W-We've got trouble!!
The angels! The angels...!
Kabuso?!
That wound! We need to treat it!
Wait, why are you here?! You should be with Nekomata...
It can't be...!
Yes, the angels attacked our hideout...
...and killed Nekomata!!
What?!
>Kabuso's words instantly freeze the air.
Th-That's a lie! It must be!!
H-Hold on. You said "hideout"...
Isn't that where our injured soldiers and citizens...
Yes, the very same. Everyone...was likely killed by angels.
I fought tooth and claw but was asked to deliver a message.
"The king can save us... Call him here..."
But by the time I left, most of our comrades were already...
So, I...I'm the only one left... *Sniff*
*Sob*
Kabuso...
Are you quite done?
If so, let's finalize our deal—
Bastard! How can you say that?!
Do you realize what you've done?!
You are the ones who opposed us.
You should have anticipated this outcome.
On the battlefield, yes! But the others were different!!
Why kill those who couldn't or wouldn't fight?!
Enough!
We mustn't delay this pact any further.
The king has spoken, and it is our role to obey...
>As the demon soldiers fall silent,
> they desperately try to quell their inner fury.
My apologies, Sir Camael. Let's continue.
Together, our armies will...
...will...
Try all you want, but it's useless if you can't save everyone.
You're our king.
What will you do if you can't even reassure your own people?
But...
No buts! You're the king!
It'll be all right, I promise.
No one loves this land more, so your words will reach them.
What is it? Let us proceed.
...Our kingdom's forces...
...regard you as the enemy and will rout you alongside Rahab!!
What...?
Wait, Cait Sith! That's—
Please, not another word! This is between demons and angels!
How can we cooperate after our people have been trampled?!
Their wrath is a king's wrath! My rage is their rage!
Listen well, angels!
You are invaders and savage murderers!
We will fiercely retaliate against any threat to our kingdom!
Yes, I couldn't agree more!
I'll follow wherever you lead!
I was a fool to believe we could ally with demons.
And so...!
>Camael moves to raise his sword against Cait Sith.
>Suddenly...
Connected... It's connected...!
!! That voice!
>A rift opens up in the sky.
>Rahab's enormous frame emerges from within.
*Chuckle* Success! I've returned to this world once more.
Just wait, you accursed angels and Liberators!
This time, my fangs will tear you limb from limb!
Rahab!
Woman! Why are you lot here?!
You finally appear, Rahab.
You failed the moment I realized your scheme.
Angels! Will you never cease to stand in my way?!
In that case, I'll turn the tables and end you here!
Be my guest. Now then—
*Yell*
>Cait Sith attacks Camael, whose sword is pointed at Rahab.
Ngh! Begone, foul demon!
As I said, our foe is the Divine!
I'll cut you down at first opportunity! Brace yourselves!
Please stop, Cait Sith! Right now, we need to—!
You're too late, humans. Our minds are made up.
Besides, think about it.
Could YOU cooperate with your friends' murderers?
You're not like the angels, so please stay out of this.
But if you choose to interfere...I will show no mercy.
>The demons attack Rahab and the Divine.
>The angels launch a counterattack against both foes.
Shoot! Negotiations have broken down!
Yes, things can't get any worse.
These would-be allies are now at each other's throats
while their mutual foe Rahab takes advantage.
Shit! How'd it turn out like this?!
Crying won't help anyone. What now, Megakin?
*Groan*
Not much choice. We're the only ones who can focus on Rahab.
It'll be dicey, but let's take 'im down here!
